55170461535454,0.0275564044713974,0.044754307717084885,0.014911449514329433,-0.12009189277887344,-0.009067857638001442,0.02201167866587639,-0.080348439514637,-0.01833178475499153,-0.0005389812286011875,-0.0030671805143356323,0.002757274778559804,-0.044284638017416,-0.06362023204565048,0.007093973457813263,-0.04261569306254387,0.029421113431453705,0.011767827905714512,0.10704537481069565,0.051537469029426575,0.020777132362127304,0.027487333863973618,-0.01372232474386692,0.03889692574739456,-0.05452679097652435,0.007970495149493217,-0.04951004311442375,0.11460651457309723,-0.05062481760978699,0.033973466604948044,-0.03372746706008911,0.03608359396457672,-0.07427898794412613,0.06660131365060806,0.0252212043851614,-0.013738900423049927,0.059736739844083786,-0.022691354155540466,-0.06701084971427917,-0.02810978889465332,0.006128447595983744,0.02048606425523758,0.006880961824208498,0.04024885222315788,0.0012606026139110327,-0.04608432948589325,-0.09206388145685196,-0.010106630623340607,-0.11554025113582611,-0.09059616178274155,-0.014552757143974304,0.059424642473459244,-0.026124339550733566,0.11034597456455231,0.013828132301568985],"timestamp":"2026-02-23T01:20:18.386Z","quality":1,"feedback":{"type":"positive","category":null,"comment":null,"timestamp":"2026-02-23T01:20:31.107Z"}},{"id":"mem-a82036b3-1771809640401","query":"How does compensation affect my Centrelink payment?","answer":"Compensation can significantly affect your Centrelink payments. Here are the key points regarding how it impacts your payments:\n\n1. **Types of Compensation**: Various compensation payments can affect your Centrelink payments, including:\n   - Workers compensation\n   - Motor vehicle accident compensation\n   - Public liability compensation\n   - Medical negligence compensation\n   - Personal injury or nervous shock compensation [Source 1].\n\n2. **Reporting Obligations**: You must inform Centrelink if you or your partner make a claim for any type of compensation. This includes any compensation you receive or stop receiving [Source 1][Source 6].\n\n3. **Affected Payments**: The following Centrelink payments and concession cards may be affected by compensation:\n   - Age Pension\n   - Austudy\n   - Carer Payment\n   - Disability Support Pension\n   - Farm Household Allowance\n   - JobSeeker Payment\n   - Parenting Payment\n   - Special Benefit\n   - Youth Allowance\n   - Low Income Health Care Card [Source 2][Source 4].\n\n4. **Impact on Payments**: If you receive compensation for loss of income, it may lead to a reduction or cessation of your income support payments. In some cases, you may also be required to repay past payments received from Centrelink [Source 3][Source 4].\n\n5. **Compensation Recovery**: Centrelink may recover some or all of the income support payments you received if you receive a lump sum or periodic compensation payment [Source 3][Source 4].\n\n6. **Compensation Estimator**: You can use the Centrelink compensation estimator to understand how your compensation claim may affect your payments, including any potential repayment amounts [Source 5][Source 7].\n\nIn summary, it is crucial to report any compensation claims to Centrelink, as they can affect your eligibility and the amount of your payments. If you have specific compensation details or scenarios, I can provide more tailored information.","sources":[{"file":"payments/how-compensation-affects-payments.md","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.17017300170418914},{"file":"general/our-payments-affected-compensation.md","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.18941010697771074},{"file":"general/centrelink-compensation-recovery.md","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.27343400408048346},{"file":"general/centrelink-compensation-information-for-lawyers-and-compensation-payers.md","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.2780348277692352},{"file":"general/when-to-use-centrelink-compensation-estimator.md","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.28180419134119983},{"file":"payments/how-compensation