,0.04628630727529526,-0.0036221903283149004,-0.10285744816064835,0.04931916296482086,-0.009832863695919514,-0.06954457610845566,0.030148372054100037,0.08405198156833649,-0.03924356773495674,-0.02985622175037861,-0.03374242037534714,-0.1203014999628067,0.06908167153596878,-0.04419256001710892,-0.053189896047115326,0.03006144054234028,-0.04036498814821243,-0.08990424871444702,0.041239794343709946,-0.02602514810860157],"timestamp":"2026-02-23T01:20:40.401Z","quality":1,"feedback":{"type":"positive","category":null,"comment":null,"timestamp":"2026-02-23T01:21:03.329Z"}},{"id":"mem-a82036b3-1771809659900","query":"How do I prove my identity with Centrelink?","answer":"To prove your identity with Centrelink, you need to follow these steps:\n\n1. **Create a myGov Account**: If you don't already have one, you need to create a myGov account and link it to Centrelink. You can do this by:\n   - Going to the myGov website and selecting **Create an account**.\n   - Following the prompts to enter your email address, mobile number, and creating a password along with secret questions [Source 3].\n\n2. **Provide Personal Information**: Once your myGov account is set up, you will need to provide personal details to verify your identity. This may include your name, address, and other identifying information.\n\n3. **Supporting Documents**: You may be required to provide supporting documents to confirm your identity. This can include documents like your driver's license, passport, or other official identification [Source 1].\n\n4. **Verification Process**: After submitting your information and documents, Centrelink will verify your identity. If you cannot prove your identity online, you can contact Centrelink for assistance [Source 5].\n\nMake sure to have all necessary documents ready to facilitate the process.","sources":[{"file":"payments/how-to-claim-ex-carer-allowance-child-health-care-card.md","pageStart":1,"pageEnd":1,"score":0.2914411688353417},{"file":"payments/how-to-claim-fo